caption:
[ WORLD CANCER DAY ] 

 Cancer is the second leading cause of death worldwide, with about 17 million people diagnosed and over 6 million dying each year. 

 On the occasion of World Cancer Day which falls on the 4th of February every year, we support all patients in their goal to fight this disease.

Every single one of us can make a difference, large or small, and together we can make real progress in reducing the global impact of cancer.

#Cancer #cancer_day #world_cancer_day #vic #enp #vic_enp

caption:
[ AEC 2022 | WINNERS ]

Yesterday, the curtain closed on the second edition of the Algerian Engineering Competition. After a long journey that started a week ago.

The finale was held at the National Polytechnic School, (15) teams competed for the title in (3) different themes, showing off their problem solving skills and their sharp thinking at critical moments. 

We'd like to congratulate the Winners :
- Supernova 2.0 ( Sanitary crisis)
- Phoenix ( Wildfires )
- Amen ( Water crisis )

Special thanks on behalf of all VIC members to the collaborating teams from the (4) different Wilayas and to @cmconsultingdz @bkfiredz and @amenhydgroupe for their collaboration and thank you to all the participant teams who believed in the Algerian Rebuild.

caption:
[ AEC | Phase Two ]

Back to you with the course of our second and last phase! 

 -The finale will take place in Algiers.
 -The selected teams from the previous phase will head to Algiers to prepare for their final project.
 -They will complete the projects they started in phase I.
 -Contestants will be given 2 days to prepare.
 -Same as the previous phase, Workshops will be provided by mentors and experts.
 -Competitors must present their projects to a jury of experts and will be evaluated on different criteria such as practicality, execution, and originality.
 -There will be three winning teams, one in each category.

caption:
[ AEC | Phase One ]

The Algerian Engineering Competiton is divided into two phases, here's the course of phase one! 

 - It will take place in the 6 wilayas : Algiers, Constantine, Oran, Tlemcen, Skikda and Bechar.
 -Teams can choose which theme they would like to work on.
 -Each team will be oriented to the closest wilaya to compete. 
 -The contestants have 48 hours to come up with a solution and present a prototype for the jury.
 -Participants will have direct contact with their mentors using platforms such as Discord or Slack, to discuss and structure their ideas.
 -Workshops will be provided through all this phase by mentors.
 -Fifteen teams will be selected to participate in phase II.

For more details, check out our website
Regestrations are still open, make sure to secure a place! both links are in our bio.

caption:
[ Participation terms | AEC (2021) ]

 These are the four (4) conditions any participant for the Algerian Engineering Competition (2021) needs to fulfill. 

-Participants ought to apply in the nearest Wilaya to their residency location. 

-The required age to participate is (18) years old or above. 

- The teams must have between (3) and (5) members.

 - Competitors who are registered without a team are obliged to team up on the first day. Otherwise, they will get excluded.

Make sure you read them and check them before applying for the competition. Otherwise, you'll be subject to exclusion.

accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Vision & Innovation Club on November 15, 2021 tagging @petroleumclub, @cirtec_, @ecc_club, @muhandisclub, and @auto.tech.bechar. May be an image of text.
caption:
[Theme 3 | Covid-19 impact ] 

The coronavirus disease has caused increasing challenges for healthcare professionals globally. As in many other countries, the rate of daily infections exponentially increased in Algeria, the effects of the pandemic extending to disturb all aspects of society. 

Although Algeria's healthcare system ranks among the best in Africa, it faced many difficulties. As the Covid-19 pandemic persists, finding reliable and effective ways to manage the situation is of the essence. 

#the_algerian_rebuild #COVID19 #competition #hackathon #hackathon2021 #technology #ENP #vic #students #health

accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Vision & Innovation Club on November 14, 2021 tagging @petroleumclub, @cirtec_, @ecc_club, @muhandisclub, and @auto.tech.bechar. May be an image of text.
caption:
[ Theme 2 | Lack of water resources ]

 This question of water resources is posed urgently in Algeria, underground water resources have been greatly reduced and efforts in this area remain very limited. Moreover, while underground water is reaching dangerously low levels, Seawater is not being used to satisfy the demand for water from the urban people. 

Therefore, we need to find a way to make clean water available all over the country. 

#the_algerian_rebuild #competition #hackathon #watersupply #students #Vic #ENP  #AEC #technology #problemsolving #Algeria

accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Vision & Innovation Club on November 13, 2021 tagging @petroleumclub, @cirtec_, @ecc_club, @muhandisclub, and @auto.tech.bechar. May be an image of text.
caption:
[Theme1| Wildfires ] 

The first theme we are going to tackle in this edition is wildfires! Wildfires affect many different segments of the population. Despite it being a yearly occurrence in Algeria, the country has not experienced such devastation in its recent history. 

This year’s catastrophe showed the country’s vulnerability to these kinds of disasters.

We need to take several steps to prevent the repeat of this tragedy in the future and find the right solutions for a better Algeria.

#the_algerian_rebuild #aec #vic #enp #hackathon #competiton #students #algiers #technology

caption:
The registrations for BRAIN DRAIN are open!

 A stimulating session about an important dilemma in our country, it's a great opportunity to share opinions and ideas alongside a good English practice.

If you want to take part in the debate, don't hesitate to fill out the form in the BIO!

In Arabic, the word used for “revolution” is “ثورة”, which translates to “an eruption”, like a volcanic eruption that sweeps everything in its away, and only after the fire is extinguished can we truly rebuild.

This is the case of Algeria’s revolution against the French colonial rule. After a century of pain, mourning tears are hardly any longer to be found in Algeria. One does not weep when faced with multiple murders and so much loss. One grits one's teeth and plans to fights. 

"و يا ثورة حار فيها الزّمان و في شعبها الهادئ الثّائر"
.
.
.

caption:
Algeria or Abroad? 

This is a dilemma that many highly educated Algerians face: stay and contribute to the development of the country or go overseas with more opportunities and resources. 

In other words, Brain Drain vs Brain Gain.

Welcome to our SECOND session of LET'S TALK!
This week with BRAIN DRAIN, we will discuss Human Flight Capital, as well as the many economical, societal and ethical questions it raises.

It will take place THIS THURSDAY, November 4th at 2pm, at the National Polytechnic School of Algiers.

Don't miss this interactive face-to-face session to practice your English, share your opinion and DEBATE!

English is a rich language, and some prepositions are just confusing. 

Here are some common mistakes in English, and their corrections! 

Can you think of a better way to say those sentences?

#vic #enp #vic_enp #EB #english_bubble #mistakes #english #common_mistakes #Englishlessons #language #prepositions

What is it like to be part of VIC's family? 

Four of our VICers @raaania.mk @idriss.merah @abderrahmanchalal @blrsadmou  from different departments will talk us through their respective experiences as members of the club, sharing their best moments and reflecting on past events and projects that made them fall in love with the VIC. 

Are you still hesitating to join us? This video will give you a brief glimpse of life as a VICer, Enjoy! 
 
Link in bio for the registrations.

caption:
⭕ المنظمة العالمية للصحة تصرح بأنه لا يوجد  ليومنا هذا أي علاج موصى به للوقاية أو العلاج ضد فايروس كورونا المستجد.

⭕ يمكن للاستهلاك المفرط أو الخاطئ للأدوية أن يؤدي إلى إحدى هته الحالات:

- مقاومة المضادات الحيوية بعد الاستخدام غير المناسب للمضادات الحيوية.
- نزيف خطير لمضادات التخثر.
- الاضطرابات الأيضية التي تسببها الكورتيكوستيرويدات وتأثيرها المثبط للمناعة، ما يتطلب احتياطات للاستخدام.

⭕ ومنه، وجب الالتزام بوصايا الأطباء كما أنه من الأولى الإستعانة بهم، فهم أهل الاختصاص.

⭕️ L'automédication est le fait de se procurer un médicament sans ordonnance.

⭕️ Selon l’OMS, aucun médicament spécifique n’est recommandé pour prévenir ou traiter l’infection par le nouveau coronavirus.

⭕ Les conséquences de l'automédication  abusive ou malmenée qui se fréquentent face à cette pandémie sont:

- L'antibiorésistance, suite à une utilisation inappropriée des antibiotiques.
- Le risque hémorragique des anticoagulants, en cas de contre-indication.
- Les désordres métaboliques causés par les corticoïdes et aussi leur effet immunosuppresseur, qui nécessite des précautions d'utilisation.

⭕️ D’où, la consultation du médecin est primordiale avant toute consommation de médicaments.

#Étudiants_Vs_Covid19 #sensibilisation #pandémie #covid #vic #enp

Today on the Hijri Calendar is Al- Muharram 1st, marking the beginning of the Islamic Year 1443.

 The word "Muharram" means 'forbidden', being one of the months during which Arabs forbade wars. 

It continues to be holy in Islam, for both good and bad deeds are considered greater during this month, than in other times.

caption:
[ Tech It Up | Workshops ]

Since the event is approaching, we are sharing with you the workshops we will be having! 

Starting with BRENCO! 
The workshop aims to introduce participants to the production of PCB (logic, software, process, etc.) through the implementation of a mini-board and then to tin and solder the components. This workshop will be granted to you by Mr. Ibrahim TAKDENTI! 

Secondly, a workshop will be granted to you by FADOS!
This workshop aims to introduce participants to this electronic diagnostic tool - FADOS - MULTIFUNCTIONAL ELECTRONIC BOARD TESTER, its innovative features, and how it allows you to easily and accurately detect faulty components without the need to unsolder them, and even 10 times faster than with the classic method.

Last but not least, another workshop will be provided to you by the scientific club CELEC, discussing one of the machine learning methods, deep learning, dedicated to beginners or to anyone from a related field. 

Swipe left for more details, and tell us in the comments down below what caught your eye the most! 

For those of you who want to participate in any workshop, make sure to fill out the form, the link is in our bio.

accessibility_caption: Photo by Vision & Innovation Club in Palais De La Culture Moufdi Zakaria, Alger. May be an image of text.
caption:
[ Theme N°5 | Internet of things ]

The Internet of Things, or IoT, refers to the billions of physical devices around the world that are now connected to the internet, all collecting and sharing data. It consists of web-enabled smart devices that are embedded with sensors, software, and other technologies. 

The benefits of the IoT for business depend on the particular implementation. (Agility and efficiency are usually the top considerations.) The idea is that companies should have access to more data about their products and internal systems, and a greater ability to make changes as a result.

#vic #enp #vic_enp #IoT #lead_tech_to_the_top
location: Palais De La Culture Moufdi Zakaria, Alger

An astounding 1/3 of the food produced in the world is wasted. This excessive and unsustainable food waste is a real tragedy for both our environment and our people. 

In this episode, our host @nazim_sehal and guest @brencoalgerie representative Amira IRMAL will help us understand just how serious this problem is, the considerable role we as individuals play in it, and how we can tackle the issue. 

On that note, @brencoalgerie and incubator #tek2hub is organizing the #SaveFood Challenge, in which all innovators and entrepreneurs are welcome to present new, practical ideas about food safety. 
check their account for more info! Deadline's on June 7th.

For the full episode, you can visit the platforms in BIO!

#savefoodchallenge 
#vic #enp #vic_enp #podcast #brencoXvic #foodwaste #savefood

accessibility_caption: Photo by Vision & Innovation Club on June 05, 2021. May be an image of one or more people and text that says 'INNOVATION VISION CLUB Food waste (G) VIC PODCAST Love food hate waste Today's Wastage, is tomorrow's shortage OUR GUEST Amira RMAL Automation Engineer Tek2Hub Incubator Manager Field Engineer at Schlumberger SPONSORED BY A JAMEAL'.
caption:
[ VIC PODCAST | Guest & Theme Announcement ]

Sadly, it is not an exaggeration to say that food waste is one of the biggest problems facing mankind today. 

And while food waste occurs in each stage of the supply chain, nearly 85% occurs downstream at consumer-facing businesses and homes. 

More than table manners or an annoyed mom, all this wasted food has drastic effects on the economy, the environment, and collective food security.

  In VIC PODCAST's second episode, engineer Amira IRMAL will explain this problem further, its cause and consequences, and recommend how YOU can avoid it. 

Stay tuned!

[Theme N°4 | Neuralink ]

Neuralink is a technology that can help humans interact with machines using their brains. It's a device, a Brain-Machine Interface, that could be implanted surgically into your brain and give you the ability to communicate with machines and even control them.

Neuralink might not teach us martial arts however, we could send and receive electrical signals through the brain to control machines. For the moment, the company has said that we will be able to control basic devices like smartphones, computers, and maybe even type using thoughts.

For further information about this topic or any of the others shared before, don't miss our event on the 5th of June,2021 at Le Palais De La Culture Moufdi Zakaria. #neuralink  #science  #technology  #newageinventors #lead_tech_to_the_top

caption:
[ Theme N°3 | 5G ] 

5G is the 5th generation mobile network, a new global wireless standard after the 4G network, that delivers higher multi-Gbps peak data speeds, ultra-low latency, massive network capacity, and more reliability. It enables a new kind of network that is designed to connect virtually everyone and everything (machines, objects, and devices). 5G networks provide lower prices, lower battery consumption, and lower latency than 4G wireless networks. It's because 5G uses Ultra-Wide Band (UWB) networks with higher band breadth at low energy levels. Band breadth is 4000 Mbps, which is four hundred times faster than 4G wireless networks.
 
5G is a wireless technology that offers extraordinary data capabilities, higher performance, and improved efficiency to empower users' experiences and connect new industries.

#lead_tech_to_the_top #technology #5G #network #science #internet

[ Theme N°2 | Biotechnology ] 

Biotechnology is a technology that uses biological systems, living organisms, or parts of this to develop or create different products such as agricultural products, food, animal feed, industrial materials, and medicines. This technology covers many disciplines like genetics, biochemistry, molecular biology, and many more.

Today, New technologies and products are developed every year within the fields of medicine to develop new therapies, agriculture to create genetically modified plants, biofuels, biological treatment, or industrial biotechnology to produce chemicals, paper, textiles, and food.

caption:
[Theme N°1 | AR/VR ] 

-  Virtual Reality :
Virtual Reality (VR) is the use of computer technology to create a simulated environment. It places the user inside an experience. Instead of viewing a screen in front of them, users are immersed and able to interact with 3D worlds. 

The experience is both visual, auditory, and, in some cases, haptic with the production of effects feedback. When the user is equipped with the appropriate interfaces, such as gloves or clothing, they can then experience certain sensations related to touch or certain actions (blow, impact, etc.) 

-  Augmented Reality:
Augmented Reality (AR) is a technology that lets people superimpose digital content (images, sounds, text) over a real-world environment. The uses of AR are today expanding to new sectors, such as healthcare, manufacturing, utilities, telecommunications, education, and public safety.

The primary value of augmented reality is how components of the digital world blend into a person's perception of the real world, not as a simple display of data, but through the integration of immersive sensations, which are perceived as natural parts of an environment. AR is used to enhance natural environments or situations and offer perceptually enriched experiences. 

-  Is there a difference between Virtual Reality and Augmented Reality?
VR and AR are two sides of the same coin. AR simulates artificial objects in the real-world environment, while VR creates an artificial environment to inhabit.

#lead_tech_to_the_top #Vic #ENP #tech #VR #AugmentedReality #virtualreality  #event

caption:
[ World Autism Awareness Day ]

There are, in fact, some days where the contrast of our differences may seem more apparent than others. But it is also on those days, more than ever, that it is time to fight systemic rejection and demand inclusion. 

Today, on Autism Awareness Day, we remind each other of the necessity of addressing the lack of autism awareness in our society and the urgency of changing the social and educational order to bear us all. 

Today is also to acknowledge the strength of the families fighting daily, the struggle of autistic kids to find schools each year, and others to fit into an incompatible educational system and remember the autistic adults with no support. 

Today is a reminder that some of us have to fight bigger battles, every day, and that spreading genuine awareness is only but the first step in a necessary process.

#autism #autismawareness

caption:
[ English Bubble | Session Announcement ] 

Effective communication is about understanding the intention behind the information, it sounds like it should be instinctive. But all too often, when we try to communicate with others something goes astray. We say one thing, the other person hears something else, and misunderstandings, frustration, and conflicts ensue. caption:
[ π Day ] 

"Pure mathematics is in its way the poetry of logical ideas" -Albert Einstein 

Talking about math without mentioning the famous constant π is impossible. This famous ratio, estimated to more than 22 trillion digits (and counting is infinite, like our love for pies), is the perfect symbol for our species' effort to tame infinity. 

As we learned at school, this curious little number denoted π, which was given this symbol by the great Swiss mathematician Leonhard Euler, is defined to be the ratio of a circle's circumference to its diameter. 

For some people, Pi day, which was first established by physicist Larry Shaw is an occasion to marvel circles,  but in fact, it deserves celebration for reasons beyond these: it puts infinity within our reach and it is essential for those of us interested in calculations in maths, engineering, construction, physics, and even space exploration. It's simply inevitable. 

Share with us in the comments other interesting facts you know about π!

accessibility_caption: Photo by Vision & Innovation Club on July 10, 2020.
caption:
[ Today In History ]

July 10th of every year marks the anniversary of a Serbian-American engineer/inventor, who revolutionized the world’s technology.

In 1856 when the majority of the world was still lit by candle light, a man named Nikola Tesla was born in Smiljan, Austrian empire (currently Croatia). 

He conceived a way to use alternating current to advantage while studying Engineering and physics. In 1883, he constructed his first induction motor. In '84 he arrived in NYC and helped Thomas Edison with the development of DC generators and motors. 

Tesla soon established his own laboratory, where he experimented with mechanical oscillators/generators, electrical discharge tubes, early X-ray imaging and carbon button lamps. 

He was the one who built the hydroelectric plant at Niagara Falls and proved to the world that this type of power was a practical energy source. He also experimented with cryogenic engineering, held patents that were later used to develop a transistor, recorded cosmic radio waves, discovered the resonant frequency of the earth, developed Tesla coil, remote control, fluorescent and neon Lighting, wireless telegraphy, built a wireless-controlled boat....

It is also worth mentioning that he spoke eight languages: Serbian, English, Czech, German, French, Hungarian, Italian and Latin.

Tesla received congratulatory letters from more than 70 pioneers in science and engineering, including Albert Einstein, and was also featured on the cover of Time magazine with the caption “All the world's his power house”.

On January 7th 1943, at the age of 86, Tesla died alone in his hotel room due to a coronary thrombosis. His body was later found by a maid after she had entered Tesla's room, ignoring the "Do Not Disturb" sign that he had placed.

  Today, 58 years later, we celebrate this day and honour the still living legacy of millions of selfless men and women: warriors of liberty, those Algerians, fellow Africans, Europeans or Asians who supported and fought for the Algerian cause, who offered everything they could, from their words to their souls, so we can be born proud and free of all shackles. 

May we be worthy of your sacrifices. May we fight and rise up against all injustices. May we be united, and make Algeria as great and righteous as you were.

"Important things are not done by impulse but by a series of small events brought together"
A quote like this would normally serve as an inspiration for us. 
However, in times like these, we ought to consider it as an omen.

On December 31 last year, China recorded several cases of unusual pneumonia in Wuhan caused by an unknown virus. Today, COVID-19 has spread to 177 countries, killing at least 11000 people and infected more than 275000 worldwide, mostly in china and italy. How did we get here? 
Indubitably, epidemics happen to serve as an accurate example of geometric progression, when a virus spreads through a population, it keeps doubling until it reaches a climax and studies have shown that this virus follows a progression where every infected person infects 2 to 2.5 people. 
Unfortunately, as human beings, this kind of progression creates some serious challenges in our daily lives that, in order to avoid the worst, one must abandon one's neglectful side and admit the fact that an imminent danger is on everyone's doorstep. 
Finally we should realize that it's better safe than sorry, because too much of the time sorry means ruined and dead. 
#Stayhome

accessibility_caption: Photo by Vision & Innovation Club on March 18, 2020.
caption:
COVID-19 is a newly discovered strain of Coronaviruses, a large family of viruses that cause illness ranging from the common cold to more severe diseases. COVID-19 causes respiratory illness, and its symptoms include fever, cough, breathing difficulties and in more severe cases, pneumonia, which can lead to death if caught by an idividual with a week immune system  As you all know, Algerian hospitals are not equipped enough to deal with a massive disease outbreak, the consequences of one occurring not be merciful. You must also know that as some people with a good immune system might be safe, they could still infect their surroundings (family and friends) and hurt them badly. So as deaths are increasing, we feel the need to remind you all to take extra measures in order to protect yourselves, and the people around you :
- Wash your hands frequently with alcohol based hand rub. (Or soap)
- Maintain a 1 meter distance from all people, and AVOID CONTACT. - Avoid touching your mouth, nose, and eyes. - Follow good respiratory hygiene. (Cover your mouth while coughing/sneezing)
- STAY HOME as long as you don't have URGENT matters to attend to. 
May Allah protect us all, and may the sick recover fast inshallah.

You might know it as the ratio of the circumference of a circle to its diameter.
It also might bring up to your mind Albert Einstein’s birthday, or even Stephen Hawking’s death .

It’s this infinite irrational wonder that has been studied in every millennial since the times of Archimedes. 
PI’s generally associated with circles. Nevertheless, it goes way further than geometric concerns. It has served, and is still serving, various fields such as arts, biology, mathematics, physics, engineering, astronomy and space exploration. Its digits are not repetitive, 40 of them would give us an estimate of the Milky Way’s circumference. Is its complex manner intriguing ? Yes, infinitely.

- Name : Erasmus+ Exchange program - Location : Europe
- To apply you need to consult with your organisation, institution, or educational establishment (for example your university).
*This exchange program is available every year. - Details : 
Erasmus+ is an international exchange program between different countries of the world and the Europian Union. It gives the opportunity to students at Bachelor and Master levels to take a full degree abroad which can take up to two years (for medecine or architecture students), actually it depends on the school or the university in which you study in your country.
Erasmus is available in more than 30 Europian countries where you can go study there, meet new international people, have different experiences and learn new languages and different cultures. You can also combine your period spent studying abroad with a traineeship to gain work experience.
You can benefit of an exchange abroad with Erasmus+ multiple times, either as a student or as a trainee, but your total time abroad may not exceed 12 months within one cycle of study.
You may also receive an Erasmus+ grant as a contribution to your travel and subsistence costs which may vary according to different situations.
-------------------------------
If you are interested and want to have more information, check their website down below to know more about the conditions, the application procedures and much more.

Here is a testimony delivered to you by Noreddine Belhadj Chikh who will share with you his experience as Erasmus+ exchange student in Spain.

https://ec.europa.eu/programmes/erasmus-plus/opportunities/individuals/students/studying-abroad_en

Note: this scholarship is available every year. - Details : "" STIPENDIUM HUNGARICUM"" is a scholarship programme for foreign students, fully-funded by the Hungarian gouvernment to attract international students and to promote education at Hungarian universities.

This programme aims to promote cultural underestanding as well as strengthen economic and cultural relations between Hungary and other countries. It's based on bilateral education cooperation agreements signed between the ministries responsible in the sending country/territories and Hungary, or between institutions. 
Currently around 70 sending partners (including ALGERIA) are engaged in the programme. 
It provides an education of a high quality, and its degree is well recognized throughout Europe and beyond. ------------------------------- If you are interested , check their website for further information about the conditions , the application procedures and much more. *Applications for September 2020 are now open and it's divided in 4 rounds :  Round 1 : deadline in 23 November 2019.  Round 2 : deadline in 07 February 2020.  Round 3 : deadline in 27 March 2020.  Round 4 : deadline in 12 June 2020.

Mandela Centennial Scholarship Programme is a fully funded scholarship, given to 100 outstanding young Africans from disadvantaged backgrounds, in order to honor President Mandela’s legacy and carry forward the important work he began in education.

-One year mandatory Leadership Core Programme before moving on to degree programmes of their choice.
-Bachelor’s degree in :-Computer Science. -Entrepreneurship. -Global Challenges. -International Business and Trade.

The scholarship covers full tuition fees, from attending African Leadership University (ALU) to airfare and all living expenses.

accessibility_caption: Photo by Vision & Innovation Club on December 09, 2019. May be an image of text that says 'VISION NNOVATION ION CLUB STEPS students who want to study abroad after graduation 95% YES NO 5% f /vic.enpa /vc -enp @vic.enp VICENP www.vic-enp.club club'.
caption:
[S.T.E.P.S |Statistics]

S.T.E.P.S is about going abroad either by getting a scolarship or through an exchange program. That's why we wanted to know whether you guys are thinking of having a new experience beyond borders. So, we conducted a survey, in which we asked students of different majors (especially technical ones) from multiple universities and schools a variety of questions, the results were quite thrilling! 
90% of our sample students want to study abroad. When asked about the reason behind that, 50% of them said that it's because they are passionate about studies and are trying to get more degrees, for 70%, it's because they long for a new experience, 20% said that it's mainly due to people's strong recommendation, and finally, 20% confessed that leaving the country is their prime reason. 
We also asked them about what they want to do after graduation, and apparently 50% want to start a career, 20% of them want to found a startup, and 20% want to try reaserch ! The rest are willing to get some experience before building their own company. 
70% of the surveyed students knew what an exchange program is, but only 10% participated in one before, they confirmed though that it was an unforgettable experience, in which they got to developp themselves personally, mentally and professionally. 
Finally, we asked about different organisations, 70% of them are familiar with AISCEC, 50% know about US exchange programms, 10% know ALGHURAIR and 20% have never heard of any of those. 
BUT don't worry, S.T.E.P.S will definitely give you all the information you need about those exchange programs, different scolarships, and MANY other surprises. 
STAY TUNED !

Studying abroad is one of the most beneficial experiences for a college student on so many levels: academically, professionally, and personally. And that’s through offering multiple opportunities to learn new languages, travel, develop one's career, discover new cultures and make new acquaintances.

According to the international Organisation for Economic Co-operation and Development (OECD) : the number of international students worldwide rose from 0.8 millions in 1975 to 3.7 millions in 2009. Unesco’s Institute for Statistics finds as well that the number is increasing approximately by 12% with each passing year.

A study made by the Institute of International Education showed that, unsurprisingly, The United States attracts most of those international students (Precisely California, New York or Texas mostly). Here's a map showing the top 10 popular destinations :

accessibility_caption: Photo by Vision & Innovation Club on November 18, 2019.
caption:
Hacking is a very confusing topic, yet it’s very practical in our days. More and more people are getting hacked everyday and it’s difficult for a typical user to tell if their computer or account is being hacked.  Well, in fact, The Vision and Innovation Club comes with another training in which we’ll show you the « Behind The Scenes » of the hacking world and the tests you should carry out to protect yourself and people you know from being a victim of these attacks.

And in this training we’ll focus on Pentesting 101.

What is « Pentesting 101» ?

Pentesting 101, or Penetration Test, is the process of seeking on network, conducting scans and testing the computer system in order to locate any weak points that could be exploited by wicked hackers.

The training doesn’t rely on any previous knowledge, it will start with the most basics, so don’t miss your chance.

It will take place on Saturday,  23th of November, 2019, at Ecole Nationale Polytechnique.

Registrations will be opened very soon and places are very limited so, stay tuned.

caption:
Tech facts #7: Industrial Technology.

Industrial technology is a field of study designed to prepare technical and management professionals for employment in manufacturing and distribution industries, education, and government.

Industrial technology is primarily involved with the management, operation, and maintenance of complex technological systems, including: Materials, Manufacturing Processes, Management, Economics, Human Relations, Quality Control, Computer Applications/CAD/CAM, and Electronics and Automation.

Industrial Technology includes wide-ranging subject matter and could be viewed as an amalgamation of industrial engineering and business topics with a focus on practicality and management of technical systems with less focus on actual engineering of those systems.

Studies in this area often employ a multi-disciplinary research methodology and shade off into the wider analysis of business and economic growth. The studies are often based on a mixture of industrial field research and desk-based data analysis and aim to be of interest and use to practitioners in business management and investment as well as academics. In engineering, construction, textiles, food and drugs, chemicals and petroleum, and other industries, the focus has been on not only the nature and factors facilitating and hampering the introduction and utilization of new technologies but also the impact of new technologies on the production organization of firms and various social and other wider aspects of the technological development process.

accessibility_caption: Photo by Vision & Innovation Club on April 26, 2019.
caption:
Tech facts #6: Networking

Today's topic in "tech facts" is well known since nowadays everything is connected and the planet has gradually been covered by computer networks of various kinds.

The concept of networking is wide but we can define it simply as connecting devices so that they can share files, printers, applications, and other computer-related resources. 
A network connects computers, mobile phones...etc
Switches, routers, and wireless access points are the essential networking basics. Through them, devices connected to your network can communicate with one another and with other networks, like the Internet.

There are several types of networks such as Local Area Networks(LANs), Wide Area Networks (WANs)and the Internet,
which are implemented in different networking architectures. 
There are many ways in which a computer network can be designed. Network architecture refers to how computers are organized in a system and how tasks are allocated between these computers. Two of the most widely used types of network architecture are peer-to-peer and client/server. Client/server architecture is also called 'tiered' because it uses multiple levels.

A Instagram post will not be enough to discuss such a contemporary topic, for that reason there will be a conference about it in Tech It Up, just so you'd learn more about it, so don't miss it.

caption:
Tech fact #5: Quantum Computing.

We are here another time with a new interesting technology fact which is Quantum Computing, you will have the chance to know more about it in this post.
Today’s computers are all based on classical physics but they are limited by locality because the classical physics tells us that systems can be in only one state at the time. However, modern quantum physics states that the world behaves differently. 
Quantum computing studies theoretical computation systems (simply called quantum computers) that make direct use of quantum-mechanical phenomena, such as superposition and entanglement, to perform operation on data.
All computing systems rely on a fundamental ability to store and manipulate information. Current computers manipulate individual bits, which store information as binary 0 and 1 states. Quantum computers leverage quantum mechanical phenomena to manipulate information. To do this, they rely on quantum bits, or qubits.
One of the most promising applications of quantum computers is for simulating the behavior of matter down to the molecular level. Auto manufacturers like Volkswagen and Daimler are using quantum computers to simulate the chemical composition of electrical-vehicle batteries to help find new ways to improve their performance.
It could take quite a few years for quantum computers to achieve their full potential. But, if these exotic new computing machines live up to their promise, they could transform entire industries and turbocharge global innovation.

accessibility_caption: Photo by Vision & Innovation Club on April 20, 2019.
caption:
TECH FACT #3

Here is a riddle for you!
I am a person-like but no human, I do the work I am made for, with precision, I do not get tired nor do I complain. So, who am I?
Yes! Easy, I am a robot and here are some facts about robotics.
Robotics is the science and study of robots that comes from the Czech word “robota”. A man-made machine that can perform work or other actions, either automatically or by a remote control.

Unlike most of people think, robotics is not a modern day invention, but in reality, automations were created for everything since the ancient civilizations. In the late 1400s Leonardo da Vinci sketched plans for a humanoid robot. Jacques de Vaucanson was famous in the 18th century for his automated human figure that played the flute and for a duck that could flap its wings.

In 1956 George Devoland Joseph Engelberger formed the world's first robot company. By the 1960s modern robots were introduced to the world.

Man gets tired, bored or even sick by doing the same thing again and again. This is why most robots today are used to do repetitive actions or jobs considered too dangerous for humans. Vehicles, canned food, clothes or anything that comes to your mind is today made by robots programmed to do so. Lately, robots broke into the world of medicine, military, or literally to another world by exploring other planets. Robotic technology has helped people who have lost arms or legs. Robots are a great tool to help mankind.

caption:
Because we're just as fascinated by technology as you are, we've decided to share with you some technological facts, Tech facts.

Tech facts #1

Most of us know Artificial Intelligence, or AI for short, only from movies like Terminator or Her, but do we know what it really is ?

In the 1940s and 50s, a handful of scientists from a variety of fields (mathematics, psychology, engineering, economics and political science) began to discuss the possibility of creating an artificial brain. The field of artificial intelligence research was founded as an academic discipline in 1956. 
Artificial intelligence is the simulation of human intelligence processes by machines, especially computer systems. These processes include learnin
g (the acquisition of information and rules for using the information), reasoning (using rules to reach approximate or definite conclusions) and self-correction. Particular applications of AI include expert systems, speech recognition and machine vision.

Artificial Intelligence became shortly the technological trend that many companies are trying to integrate into their business, time, money and energy are all invested into advancing this technology, it's a very controversial subject, because while many think it's revolutionary, for many others it seems too strange and more of a sci-fi than reality, and they tend to be afraid of it, scared of their own creation's ability to be independent in taking its own decisions, even Elon Musk fears AI, "AI is a fundamental risk to the existence of human civilization", he said, it's obvious that as soon as we surpass this controversy, AI will make an unpredictable leap, for good or bad though ? we do not know.

technology, noun
/tɛkˈnɒlədʒi/ -machinery and equipment developed from the application of scientific knowledge. -the practical application of knowledge especially in a particular area. -the specialized aspects of a particular field of endeavor. "Any sufficiently advanced technology is undistinguishable from magic", British astronomer and writer Arthur C. Clarke said, it's obvious to see how much effect this magic called technology has had on our everyday life, it's practically everywhere, so what's your favourite magical domain ? Yours is not among the options ? Tell us in the comments.

accessibility_caption: Photo by Vision & Innovation Club on April 06, 2019.
caption:
It's been 3 years since Lead-H Tech's 2nd edition in 2016, organized by VIC, made a huge success, gathering together both technology enthusiasts and science leaders alike, and now it's back, with even more of what made it so successful, as Tech It Up.
Tech It Up is an invention showcase, a technology convention, and a crossroads of brilliant ideas and minds, it offers the opportunity for these talents to promote their innovations and share with the world their future prospects.
Whether you're a young inventor, an expert in your field, or a tech enthusiast, Tech It Up is for you, bringing together all those concerned by technology's various fields, as a perfect opprotunity to either present your projects and meet other fellow inventors, or to meet the exhibitors and revel in their ideas.
The event will be held on May the fourth, in the National Polytechnic School of Algiers.
TAKE TECHNOLOGY TO THE TOP

Further details will be shared

As we promised, the time has come. Speakers' Registrations are finally here. ( link in bio) 
Igniting and enlightenment starts now, and the first step to do so is to register now. 
What are waiting for! Places are so limited. 
RULES ARE SIMPLE : 5 minutes presentation, 20 slides, 15 seconds for each slide  You can use  the language that you like (Français, Englais, العربية)

This is your chance to improve your public speaking skills , to have an amazing experience and to pass an unforgetable day with us . don't hesitate ! 
The official speakers will be chosen according to the quality of their presentation, and their experience with public speaking

Ps : AS WE MENTIONED BEFORE, THE THEME IS : "ART", THUS, THE PRESENTATIONS SHOULD BE RELATED TO ART IN A WAY OR ANOTHER, DON't THINK OF IT AS A LIMITED SUBJECT BUT THINK OUTSIDE THE BOX, ART CAN BE FOUND EVERYWHERE, NOT JUST MUSIC AND DRAWING AND SUBJECTS LIKE THIS, BUT OF COURSE THESE ONES COUNT AS WELL.

[ ignite | 27th of April ]

Art , the simple three-lettered word, has a broad definition. From photography to music to dance to painting, everything is a form of art. Creating something without words, something that speaks to people. Art is a language of its own. As simple as it may sound, it is actually something infinite, you can write books talking about it and still not give it what it deserves.

For this particular reason, we already announced that ART is our theme for this edition , not to limit you neither to upset you, since you believe that anything in our lives has an artistic side, you still can talk about anything you want. 
We gladly ask you to react and comment below what's on your mind about Art , and what kind of Art you prefer watching speakers talking about . 
Stay tuned , registrations for speakers are close to be opened than never ! 
Start the Enlightenment already.

[IGNITE ENP | 27 of APRIL] " Art enables us to find ourselves and lose ourselves at the same time" <Thomas Merton>

For its second edition, Ignite ENP comes to you wearing the suit of:  ART
Art is not an action or an object, but an internal appreciation of balance and harmony, and therefore
an aspect of being a human beyond utility.

Public speaking itself is Art, to say words that touch the heart and the soul is not easy,
because we as humans, may forget what someone said or what someone did, BUT we will never forget when someone 
makes us FEEL.

Make sure you allocate time to appreciate and notice Art around you, learn how to speak this common language between all people
because after all, ART is everywhere, around us, ART IS WITHIN US !

accessibility_caption: Photo by Vision & Innovation Club on March 14, 2019.
caption:
Pi is an infinite, non-repeating decimal – meaning that every possible number combination exists somewhere in pi.  Converted into ASCII text, somewhere in that string of digits is the name of every person you will ever love, the date, time, and manner of your death, and the answers to all the great questions of the universe.  Converted into a bitmap, somewhere in that infinite string of digits is a pixel-perfect representation of the first thing you saw on this earth, the last thing you will see before your life leaves you, and all the moments, momentous and mundane, that will occur between those points.

All information that has ever existed or will ever exist, the DNA of every being in the universe.

EVERYTHING: all contained in the ratio of a circumference and a diameter.

#VIC #we_lead_the_VICtory

caption:
Are you a field engineer and looking to get experience? Wants to learn softwares that would be useful in your career? 
VIC is here to help you with the ARCGIS training.

This software is a system composed of different platforms that allows users wether desktop web or mobile to collaborate and share geographic information.

ARCGIS design training, you can think of it as a series of programs and software tools that you use to perform professional geographic information systems work. It will also provide participants with an opportunity to learn how to solve problems, make better decisions, anticipate and manage change, communicate more effectively

The training will be held thursday, Saturday,7th ,9th at the Ecole Nationale Polytechnique, in the Civil Engineering Department Amphitheater @ 9 A.M.
https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSc7Y9xfUia3vEeXPJruGr6q5KmBVo9m51s8QFETWirGxzY6oQ/viewform

caption:
[ Android Design Training ]

The Vision and Innovation Club is back with the first training of the year 2019: The Android Design training. 
Have you always wondered about android applications? or had any idea about them but had no clue how to realize them? 
This is your chance then!
The Android design training will discuss the concept of User Experience Design and its importance in the process of building a product for a company and will also be a chance for participants to learn Design Thinking and User Centered Thinking 
The training will be concluded with a workshop in order to give the participants a chance to practice their newfound knowledge on their own.

The training will be held Saturday, February 2nd, at the Ecole Nationale Polytechnique, in the Civil Engineering Department Amphitheater @ 9 A.M.

The registrations link is in the BIO.

accessibility_caption: Photo by Vision & Innovation Club on August 06, 2018.
caption:
[ AEC | What is AEC? ]
The AEC (Algerian Engineering Competition) is a national competition between different universities and engineering schools in Algeria, organized by the Vision & Innovation Club. Divided into 2 sub-competitions, it aims to bring together teams of students to try to solve real given problems by industrial companies and experts.
It's the first of its kind because no other engineering competition has ever been organized in Africa.
#AEC
#VIC

caption:
Still confused about Engineers' Gala? what is this event? What am I going to gain if I participate?A lot of questions you're holding inside you? Don't worry 😉😎 From today, we are presenting a series of testimonies of last year's participants, through which we hope that you, our dear community, can live the experience through their perspectives and get a better idea about it.

The first testimony is by :Yanis Otmani

#Engineers_Gala_2nd_Edition 
#VIC_ENP #engineers_gala

The Engineers' Gala at first was only an idea 💡, that became a goal 📈which was molded into a projet 🎊 , to be finally an amazing opportunity for all graduates or aspiring engineers that opened the door to their careers and their mindsets.

Only two weeks left to this year's second edition, seize the opportunity and engage with your peers in this unique event 🤩😎😀. #Networking 
#Engineers_Gala_2nd_Edition #engineers_gala 
#VIC
